WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.809 align:middle line:90%
[ Music ]

00:00:16.283 --> 00:00:20.688 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa Garr: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr
host of Gaiam Inspirations.

00:00:20.688 --> 00:00:24.458 align:middle line:84%
So what is an ex-emergency
medicine doctor have to say

00:00:24.458 --> 00:00:25.559 align:middle line:90%
about the exploration

00:00:25.559 --> 00:00:28.596 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness and
self-realization?

00:00:28.596 --> 00:00:29.930 align:middle line:90%
Well, a lot.

00:00:29.930 --> 00:00:33.134 align:middle line:84%
The age of 30, my guess, Richard
Moss had a transformative

00:00:33.134 --> 00:00:37.404 align:middle line:84%
realization that transformed his
life from practicing medicine

00:00:37.404 --> 00:00:40.908 align:middle line:84%
to transmitting healing
energy to others

00:00:40.908 --> 00:00:43.277 align:middle line:90%
through touch and through voice.

00:00:43.277 --> 00:00:46.680 align:middle line:84%
And today, Richard Moss
teaches experiential workshops

00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:49.917 align:middle line:84%
of what he calls deep work
to thousands of people

00:00:49.917 --> 00:00:51.886 align:middle line:90%
in 20 different countries.

00:00:51.886 --> 00:00:52.720 align:middle line:90%
Welcome.

00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:54.121 align:middle line:90%
>> Richard Moss: Thank you Lisa.

00:00:54.121 --> 00:00:56.223 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa Garr: I can tell this is
going to be an amazing interview

00:00:56.223 --> 00:00:59.760 align:middle line:84%
because in your presence
there is a certain vibration

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:03.397 align:middle line:84%
that is increasing just
by sitting next to you.

00:01:03.397 --> 00:01:04.832 align:middle line:90%
What is that?

00:01:04.832 --> 00:01:07.001 align:middle line:90%
What is that?

00:01:07.001 --> 00:01:09.737 align:middle line:84%
>> Richard Moss: That's what
awakened in me when I was 30.

00:01:09.737 --> 00:01:12.473 align:middle line:84%
It's-- You know, people talk
about cosmic consciousness.

00:01:12.473 --> 00:01:13.474 align:middle line:90%
There's different words for it.

00:01:13.474 --> 00:01:16.043 align:middle line:90%
I didn't even know it existed.

00:01:16.043 --> 00:01:18.112 align:middle line:84%
It was a very rough
ride for awhile.

00:01:18.112 --> 00:01:19.313 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa Garr: Yeah.

00:01:19.313 --> 00:01:21.048 align:middle line:84%
>> Richard Moss: But when
you read Walt Whitman

00:01:21.048 --> 00:01:25.119 align:middle line:84%
and you read the "Song of
Myself" and his "Leaves

00:01:25.119 --> 00:01:29.022 align:middle line:84%
of Grass", when you read the
book "Cosmic Consciousness",

00:01:29.022 --> 00:01:32.693 align:middle line:84%
it's kind of like a puberty,
but it's a spiritual puberty

00:01:32.693 --> 00:01:34.861 align:middle line:84%
and it doesn't take
away who you were.

00:01:34.861 --> 00:01:37.565 align:middle line:84%
It's as if suddenly like
when we have puberty

00:01:37.565 --> 00:01:42.269 align:middle line:84%
and our body has changed,
this is tremendous, new--

00:01:42.269 --> 00:01:43.671 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa Garr: Energy.

00:01:43.671 --> 00:01:47.274 align:middle line:84%
>> Richard Moss: -- energy and a
capacity to think and integrate

00:01:47.274 --> 00:01:51.078 align:middle line:84%
and listen, intuition,
and perception.

00:01:51.078 --> 00:01:52.111 align:middle line:90%
It's--

00:01:52.111 --> 00:01:53.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa Garr: It's
as if there's energy

00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:55.316 align:middle line:84%
that you don't know
where to place yet.

00:01:55.316 --> 00:01:56.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Richard Moss: Well,

00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:58.885 align:middle line:84%
I know that my field can
literarily turn a room

00:01:58.885 --> 00:02:02.423 align:middle line:84%
of restless people
dead still in minutes.

00:02:02.423 --> 00:02:08.295 align:middle line:84%
And so basically the agency
for my work is something both

00:02:08.295 --> 00:02:10.664 align:middle line:84%
that emanates through
me and then the things

00:02:10.664 --> 00:02:13.133 align:middle line:84%
that I teach people to learn
how to do for themselves.

00:02:13.133 --> 00:02:17.204 align:middle line:84%
Because what happened to me,
I can't reproduce for anyone.

00:02:17.204 --> 00:02:20.007 align:middle line:84%
But my whole work is built
around trying to bring people

00:02:20.007 --> 00:02:22.543 align:middle line:84%
in to such an immediate
experience with being

00:02:22.543 --> 00:02:26.247 align:middle line:84%
in the now, being present, being
what I called radically alive,

00:02:26.247 --> 00:02:28.782 align:middle line:90%
and that's what you're feeling.

00:02:28.782 --> 00:02:29.617 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: It is.

00:02:29.617 --> 00:02:30.584 align:middle line:90%
I am absolutely feeling that.

00:02:30.584 --> 00:02:32.620 align:middle line:84%
It's very transformative
experience.

00:02:32.620 --> 00:02:35.055 align:middle line:84%
It is. And you gave
the exact center

00:02:35.055 --> 00:02:37.558 align:middle line:84%
where it's happening
in my solar plexus.

00:02:37.558 --> 00:02:40.261 align:middle line:84%
So, take me back
to that experience

00:02:40.261 --> 00:02:43.597 align:middle line:84%
when you are an ER doctor
and you had this type

00:02:43.597 --> 00:02:45.866 align:middle line:90%
of surge coming to a room

00:02:45.866 --> 00:02:49.036 align:middle line:84%
where there was probably not
a lot permission for that.

00:02:49.036 --> 00:02:52.139 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: You know the first
time it really took me was

00:02:52.139 --> 00:02:56.410 align:middle line:84%
when I was coming to a patient
in the ER and I was going

00:02:56.410 --> 00:03:00.581 align:middle line:84%
to sedate him and keep him for
observation and a voice said

00:03:00.581 --> 00:03:01.749 align:middle line:84%
to me-- there was
a nurse next to me

00:03:01.749 --> 00:03:04.151 align:middle line:84%
with some syringes
to give medication.

00:03:04.151 --> 00:03:06.420 align:middle line:84%
This voice in my head that
I've never heard before said,

00:03:06.420 --> 00:03:09.957 align:middle line:84%
"You have nothing to share
with this man except love."

00:03:09.957 --> 00:03:12.760 align:middle line:84%
So he's good, big guy
with two policeman there

00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:17.131 align:middle line:84%
because he had been violent
and I just said to him,

00:03:17.131 --> 00:03:18.899 align:middle line:84%
"I can't imagine what
you're actually feeling.

00:03:18.899 --> 00:03:22.970 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to touch you so softly
that it can possibly hurt you."

00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:26.073 align:middle line:84%
I put my hand just above his
head and my hand on his belly.

00:03:26.073 --> 00:03:27.574 align:middle line:90%
I got blazing hot.

00:03:27.574 --> 00:03:28.409 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:03:28.409 --> 00:03:29.276 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: The room got blazing hot.

00:03:29.276 --> 00:03:30.678 align:middle line:90%
The policeman opened the window.

00:03:30.678 --> 00:03:35.349 align:middle line:84%
The man's eyes rolled back in
his head and half an hour later

00:03:35.349 --> 00:03:38.118 align:middle line:84%
when he woke up, he
was completely fine

00:03:38.118 --> 00:03:39.853 align:middle line:90%
and we discharged him.

00:03:39.853 --> 00:03:41.822 align:middle line:84%
And I went home and
said to myself,

00:03:41.822 --> 00:03:43.257 align:middle line:90%
"What in the world was that?"

00:03:43.257 --> 00:03:44.458 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: What happened?

00:03:44.458 --> 00:03:45.859 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And what does that
mean, you have nothing

00:03:45.859 --> 00:03:48.162 align:middle line:90%
to share with this man?

00:03:48.162 --> 00:03:49.363 align:middle line:90%
What kind of love is that?

00:03:49.363 --> 00:03:51.565 align:middle line:90%
What kind-- that you-- So that--

00:03:51.565 --> 00:03:53.834 align:middle line:84%
After that I started
really thinking it's time

00:03:53.834 --> 00:03:55.636 align:middle line:84%
to have a leave of
absence for medicine.

00:03:55.636 --> 00:03:59.707 align:middle line:84%
And then I had a dream and it
made it really obvious to me

00:03:59.707 --> 00:04:02.276 align:middle line:84%
that I-- it was time
for me to start living

00:04:02.276 --> 00:04:04.678 align:middle line:84%
out of myself instead of
that of what I'd memorized

00:04:04.678 --> 00:04:06.013 align:middle line:90%
to become a physician.

00:04:06.013 --> 00:04:07.281 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Were you having
an inter-conflict

00:04:07.281 --> 00:04:09.583 align:middle line:90%
with medicine prior to that or?

00:04:09.583 --> 00:04:11.085 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: In a certain sense, yes.

00:04:11.085 --> 00:04:15.122 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I knew psychologically
I didn't really belong

00:04:15.122 --> 00:04:15.923 align:middle line:90%
in medicine.

00:04:15.923 --> 00:04:16.889 align:middle line:90%
It was a natural step form.

00:04:16.889 --> 00:04:18.425 align:middle line:90%
My mother had been a nurse.

00:04:18.425 --> 00:04:19.626 align:middle line:90%
It was the Vietnam War.

00:04:19.626 --> 00:04:21.762 align:middle line:90%
It was fascinating to me.

00:04:21.762 --> 00:04:25.632 align:middle line:84%
I had never regretted one
minute being a doctor.

00:04:25.632 --> 00:04:27.901 align:middle line:84%
I didn't particularly like the
educational process 'cause it

00:04:27.901 --> 00:04:29.503 align:middle line:84%
was that time and
probably is still

00:04:29.503 --> 00:04:32.639 align:middle line:84%
in some degree, very
soul-deadening.

00:04:32.639 --> 00:04:35.409 align:middle line:84%
But the actual--
once you finished

00:04:35.409 --> 00:04:39.013 align:middle line:84%
that educational process, the
opportunity to be with people

00:04:39.013 --> 00:04:41.615 align:middle line:90%
and help them is just wonderful.

00:04:41.615 --> 00:04:42.783 align:middle line:90%
And my life has been saved

00:04:42.783 --> 00:04:44.918 align:middle line:84%
by modern medicine
a number of times.

00:04:44.918 --> 00:04:47.788 align:middle line:84%
So I'm profoundly
respectful for it,

00:04:47.788 --> 00:04:49.823 align:middle line:84%
love the way it's evolving
and I know it's not--

00:04:49.823 --> 00:04:51.091 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: The educational process,

00:04:51.091 --> 00:04:53.227 align:middle line:84%
it's mostly wrote
memorization without--

00:04:53.227 --> 00:04:56.630 align:middle line:84%
with the absence of the
actual field of a human.

00:04:56.630 --> 00:04:58.999 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Well, I remember there
was-- I think the dean of Yale

00:04:58.999 --> 00:05:00.534 align:middle line:90%
or Johns Hopkins giving a talk

00:05:00.534 --> 00:05:03.170 align:middle line:84%
to another graduating medical
school class a long time ago

00:05:03.170 --> 00:05:05.406 align:middle line:84%
and he said, "Half of what
we taught you is wrong.

00:05:05.406 --> 00:05:06.607 align:middle line:90%
We just don't know which half."

00:05:06.607 --> 00:05:08.675 align:middle line:90%
[ Laughter ]

00:05:08.675 --> 00:05:09.810 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Very true.

00:05:09.810 --> 00:05:11.879 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: But the beauty
of it is that the nature

00:05:11.879 --> 00:05:15.949 align:middle line:84%
of scientific empirical
exploration is

00:05:15.949 --> 00:05:19.420 align:middle line:84%
that when you start with
something, it's a hypothesis.

00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:20.788 align:middle line:90%
If it helps you use it.

00:05:20.788 --> 00:05:23.724 align:middle line:84%
If it doesn't help you stop
and we are constantly evolving,

00:05:23.724 --> 00:05:25.059 align:middle line:84%
and then it's constantly
evolving

00:05:25.059 --> 00:05:28.095 align:middle line:84%
and it's an incomplete thing,
eastern medicine has a lot

00:05:28.095 --> 00:05:32.065 align:middle line:84%
to contribute and nutrition
has a tremendous amount

00:05:32.065 --> 00:05:32.933 align:middle line:90%
to contribute.

00:05:32.933 --> 00:05:34.134 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Absolutely, yeah.

00:05:34.134 --> 00:05:36.170 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: But the greatest
suffering I think

00:05:36.170 --> 00:05:40.340 align:middle line:84%
on this planet is interpersonal,
it's relational suffering.

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:43.377 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Now, you said that
to me earlier about most

00:05:43.377 --> 00:05:45.712 align:middle line:84%
of the problems that
people come to you

00:05:45.712 --> 00:05:50.350 align:middle line:84%
with as a spiritual healer now,
I will call you, is relational.

00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:54.521 align:middle line:84%
It's about relationships and
is that intimate relationships

00:05:54.521 --> 00:05:57.424 align:middle line:84%
or relationships within
self or what types

00:05:57.424 --> 00:05:59.226 align:middle line:84%
of relationships are
we talking about?

00:05:59.226 --> 00:06:01.028 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Within a certain
sense the relationship

00:06:01.028 --> 00:06:04.331 align:middle line:84%
to yourself is inseparable from
your relationship to others

00:06:04.331 --> 00:06:08.001 align:middle line:84%
and vice versa and that
relationship depends upon a

00:06:08.001 --> 00:06:10.704 align:middle line:84%
different relationship which
is your internal relationship

00:06:10.704 --> 00:06:13.740 align:middle line:84%
to consciousness
or mystery or God.

00:06:13.740 --> 00:06:15.709 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of
different words for it.

00:06:15.709 --> 00:06:20.714 align:middle line:84%
So in essence, the closer I get
to me, the closer I get to God,

00:06:20.714 --> 00:06:22.449 align:middle line:90%
the closer I get to you.

00:06:22.449 --> 00:06:25.252 align:middle line:84%
And the distance I experience
from you if you're my husband,

00:06:25.252 --> 00:06:29.356 align:middle line:84%
my wife-- obviously I
don't have a husband,

00:06:29.356 --> 00:06:31.525 align:middle line:90%
but I mean the distance we feel

00:06:31.525 --> 00:06:33.927 align:middle line:84%
from another is actually
a mirror of the distance

00:06:33.927 --> 00:06:36.396 align:middle line:84%
from our own true
authentic selves.

00:06:36.396 --> 00:06:38.532 align:middle line:90%
So one, people don't come to me

00:06:38.532 --> 00:06:40.267 align:middle line:84%
because they have
relationship problems.

00:06:40.267 --> 00:06:42.136 align:middle line:84%
They come because
they're seekers.

00:06:42.136 --> 00:06:43.937 align:middle line:84%
They come because
they got that thorn

00:06:43.937 --> 00:06:47.307 align:middle line:84%
in their heart that's saying
there's something more in life.

00:06:47.307 --> 00:06:50.677 align:middle line:84%
I want something more,
sometimes when I was--

00:06:50.677 --> 00:06:52.746 align:middle line:84%
I first started doing
this work I was 30.

00:06:52.746 --> 00:06:56.450 align:middle line:84%
The average age of the people
with me was 48, now I'm 66.

00:06:56.450 --> 00:06:59.253 align:middle line:84%
The average ages of people that
come to my programs is again,

00:06:59.253 --> 00:07:03.690 align:middle line:84%
48, 49, 50 because that's
the time in a person's life

00:07:03.690 --> 00:07:07.861 align:middle line:84%
where everything unlived that
you had to sacrifice to be a--

00:07:07.861 --> 00:07:11.899 align:middle line:84%
have a career, be a parent,
be a homemaker, is screaming

00:07:11.899 --> 00:07:14.501 align:middle line:84%
and saying, "I want
to live now."

00:07:14.501 --> 00:07:16.737 align:middle line:84%
And people don't know how
to let go and make space

00:07:16.737 --> 00:07:20.173 align:middle line:84%
for their soul's evolution
and that's where they come

00:07:20.173 --> 00:07:24.611 align:middle line:84%
and find me and that's--
and then what we discover is

00:07:24.611 --> 00:07:28.582 align:middle line:84%
so much loneliness, so
much hunger for intimacy

00:07:28.582 --> 00:07:32.386 align:middle line:84%
in a larger sense, not
just sexual but connection.

00:07:32.386 --> 00:07:33.754 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:07:33.754 --> 00:07:37.224 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Really connection being
heard, being seen, enjoying,

00:07:37.224 --> 00:07:40.127 align:middle line:84%
you know, relationship
and they're suffering

00:07:40.127 --> 00:07:41.595 align:middle line:90%
because it's not there.

00:07:41.595 --> 00:07:43.664 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: In retrospect, looking
at the people that would come

00:07:43.664 --> 00:07:48.135 align:middle line:84%
in to the ER, did you
see them at a soul level

00:07:48.135 --> 00:07:52.673 align:middle line:84%
that they created illnesses or
emergencies because of a lack

00:07:52.673 --> 00:07:54.541 align:middle line:90%
of something in their lives?

00:07:54.541 --> 00:07:56.243 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: You know, when I read
the question that you're going

00:07:56.243 --> 00:07:59.446 align:middle line:84%
to ask me this, I loved it
because I thought to myself,

00:07:59.446 --> 00:08:04.251 align:middle line:84%
"Can I put myself back 37 years
and step back into the ER?

00:08:04.251 --> 00:08:06.219 align:middle line:90%
What did I see there?"

00:08:06.219 --> 00:08:08.956 align:middle line:84%
I saw, first of all in the
ER in those days and maybe

00:08:08.956 --> 00:08:11.792 align:middle line:90%
so true, is the poor people.

00:08:11.792 --> 00:08:18.298 align:middle line:84%
And I saw people who had
no idea what self awareness

00:08:18.298 --> 00:08:19.700 align:middle line:90%
or self reflection is.

00:08:19.700 --> 00:08:24.204 align:middle line:84%
Who had abuse their bodies
often without alcohol or drugs

00:08:24.204 --> 00:08:26.907 align:middle line:84%
who were possessed by their
tempers and lost control

00:08:26.907 --> 00:08:29.576 align:middle line:84%
and hurt themselves
or hurt others.

00:08:29.576 --> 00:08:31.612 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I saw a human suffering.

00:08:31.612 --> 00:08:33.747 align:middle line:84%
And at the time I didn't
understand the nature

00:08:33.747 --> 00:08:37.117 align:middle line:84%
of that suffering or the
cost of it but now I do.

00:08:37.117 --> 00:08:40.186 align:middle line:84%
I think at the time I
loved emergency medicine

00:08:40.186 --> 00:08:42.823 align:middle line:90%
because damn, you did something.

00:08:42.823 --> 00:08:44.124 align:middle line:90%
If I got a diagnosis right,

00:08:44.124 --> 00:08:46.093 align:middle line:84%
I remember the neurosurgeon
calling me up and said,

00:08:46.093 --> 00:08:48.228 align:middle line:84%
"That was a good diagnosis,
you save that guy."

00:08:48.228 --> 00:08:50.430 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: It's all about
diagnosis, yes, yes.

00:08:50.430 --> 00:08:52.232 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So it's very
practical and concrete

00:08:52.232 --> 00:08:53.967 align:middle line:84%
and that's what I
loved about it.

00:08:53.967 --> 00:08:56.303 align:middle line:84%
But it was not-- you
know, what I missed,

00:08:56.303 --> 00:08:58.238 align:middle line:84%
was that you never really
saw the people again.

00:08:58.238 --> 00:08:59.139 align:middle line:90%
You never got to know them.

00:08:59.139 --> 00:09:00.607 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh, yeah.

00:09:00.607 --> 00:09:03.710 align:middle line:84%
And now in that experience that
you had, that energy that came

00:09:03.710 --> 00:09:08.649 align:middle line:84%
through you, it was-- was like
a surge like I was experiencing

00:09:08.649 --> 00:09:09.783 align:middle line:90%
at the beginning of the show,

00:09:09.783 --> 00:09:14.655 align:middle line:84%
that surge of profound
enthusiasm and energy

00:09:14.655 --> 00:09:17.524 align:middle line:84%
and soul force, I
think I can call it.

00:09:17.524 --> 00:09:20.761 align:middle line:84%
Was that that came
through you at that moment?

00:09:20.761 --> 00:09:24.464 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: It came through me in
stages and finally one day

00:09:24.464 --> 00:09:26.667 align:middle line:84%
and I wrote a book called
"The Black Butterfly".

00:09:26.667 --> 00:09:29.836 align:middle line:84%
Finally, one day the
energy just became enormous.

00:09:29.836 --> 00:09:30.971 align:middle line:90%
It was overwhelming.

00:09:30.971 --> 00:09:32.339 align:middle line:84%
I thought I was going to
be annihilated and one

00:09:32.339 --> 00:09:33.540 align:middle line:90%
of the beautiful things

00:09:33.540 --> 00:09:35.909 align:middle line:84%
about having been a doctor
is I could quickly say,

00:09:35.909 --> 00:09:37.377 align:middle line:90%
"Oh, I'm not psychotic.

00:09:37.377 --> 00:09:40.280 align:middle line:84%
Oh, this is not a tumor of my
adrenal gland that's putting

00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:42.049 align:middle line:90%
out so much adrenaline."

00:09:42.049 --> 00:09:44.918 align:middle line:84%
This is something of a
phenomenological process

00:09:44.918 --> 00:09:46.353 align:middle line:90%
that doesn't belong in medicine.

00:09:46.353 --> 00:09:47.754 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Interesting.

00:09:47.754 --> 00:09:49.423 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And it is not commonly
written about, I had not come

00:09:49.423 --> 00:09:51.892 align:middle line:84%
across it in psychiatry
or psychology.

00:09:51.892 --> 00:09:53.593 align:middle line:84%
Of course since then
there are things

00:09:53.593 --> 00:09:55.896 align:middle line:84%
like spiritual emergencies,
spiritual emergence,

00:09:55.896 --> 00:09:57.230 align:middle line:90%
those kinds of terminology.

00:09:57.230 --> 00:10:00.500 align:middle line:84%
What it was, was the awakening
of the Kundalini energy

00:10:00.500 --> 00:10:03.503 align:middle line:84%
if you're an Easterner or
what I think what we would

00:10:03.503 --> 00:10:05.472 align:middle line:90%
cosmic consciousness.

00:10:05.472 --> 00:10:07.140 align:middle line:90%
And it culminated at the moment

00:10:07.140 --> 00:10:09.810 align:middle line:84%
when a black butterfly
landed right on my forehead.

00:10:09.810 --> 00:10:11.144 align:middle line:84%
I'd watched these two
butterflies [inaudible],

00:10:11.144 --> 00:10:14.948 align:middle line:84%
a dark one and a light
one mating on a branch.

00:10:14.948 --> 00:10:17.451 align:middle line:84%
I had spent three days and
nights watching my mind

00:10:17.451 --> 00:10:19.119 align:middle line:84%
because of this overwhelming
energy.

00:10:19.119 --> 00:10:21.221 align:middle line:84%
I kept saying, "This
is a thought about me.

00:10:21.221 --> 00:10:22.389 align:middle line:84%
This is a thought
about the future.

00:10:22.389 --> 00:10:24.291 align:middle line:84%
This is a thought
about the past."

00:10:24.291 --> 00:10:27.027 align:middle line:84%
And I kept myself centered
by just watching, watching,

00:10:27.027 --> 00:10:29.029 align:middle line:84%
watching day and
night, day and night.

00:10:29.029 --> 00:10:30.063 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't sleep.

00:10:30.063 --> 00:10:31.398 align:middle line:84%
I just had some much
energy within me.

00:10:31.398 --> 00:10:35.802 align:middle line:84%
The black butterfly landed
and I was one with everything.

00:10:35.802 --> 00:10:37.537 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I understood
the kingdom of heaven

00:10:37.537 --> 00:10:40.607 align:middle line:84%
of is right here, just
we rarely ever see it.

00:10:40.607 --> 00:10:42.209 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Let's talk
about that experience

00:10:42.209 --> 00:10:44.411 align:middle line:84%
where you're watching your
thoughts and listening

00:10:44.411 --> 00:10:46.613 align:middle line:84%
to what your thoughts
were about.

00:10:46.613 --> 00:10:51.017 align:middle line:84%
So, we have mind chatter
quite often in our lives.

00:10:51.017 --> 00:10:56.323 align:middle line:84%
So I'm speaking about myself,
I will, in the collect we.

00:10:56.323 --> 00:10:58.859 align:middle line:84%
Where I'm thinking about
the future or I'm thinking

00:10:58.859 --> 00:11:01.828 align:middle line:84%
about how I'm appearing
in something.

00:11:01.828 --> 00:11:06.366 align:middle line:84%
I mean those are thoughts that
run my mind most of the day.

00:11:06.366 --> 00:11:07.834 align:middle line:84%
Is that what you're
talking about?

00:11:07.834 --> 00:11:10.137 align:middle line:84%
Is that a separateness
from ourselves?

00:11:10.137 --> 00:11:10.771 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Exactly.

00:11:10.771 --> 00:11:12.072 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: It is, OK.

00:11:12.072 --> 00:11:14.508 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: The basic
thing we all know is

00:11:14.508 --> 00:11:17.477 align:middle line:84%
that there's no other time
but now, but the intellect,

00:11:17.477 --> 00:11:19.746 align:middle line:84%
the mind, the thinking
self is never in the now.

00:11:19.746 --> 00:11:22.649 align:middle line:84%
If you're in the now, you do
not think, you're just aware.

00:11:22.649 --> 00:11:23.884 align:middle line:90%
The man on the surfboard

00:11:23.884 --> 00:11:27.354 align:middle line:84%
or the woman riding a
wave, they're not thinking.

00:11:27.354 --> 00:11:29.956 align:middle line:84%
Professional athlete,
golf stroke, tennis,

00:11:29.956 --> 00:11:31.758 align:middle line:90%
whatever, they're not thinking.

00:11:31.758 --> 00:11:35.729 align:middle line:84%
They have to completely let
go and be body, environment,

00:11:35.729 --> 00:11:38.298 align:middle line:84%
action, one thing, and
that's what happened to me

00:11:38.298 --> 00:11:40.100 align:middle line:90%
when the black butterfly landed.

00:11:40.100 --> 00:11:43.370 align:middle line:84%
It became-- Everything
became one and it wasn't--

00:11:43.370 --> 00:11:44.871 align:middle line:90%
I had done a lot of athletics.

00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:48.542 align:middle line:84%
I had-- I knew what it was
to be in flow, rock climbing,

00:11:48.542 --> 00:11:51.378 align:middle line:84%
mountaineering, a
little bit on surfing.

00:11:51.378 --> 00:11:53.079 align:middle line:90%
I never became a great surfer.

00:11:53.079 --> 00:11:57.117 align:middle line:84%
But-- Then suddenly this
experience was of a whole order

00:11:57.117 --> 00:11:59.052 align:middle line:90%
of magnitude beyond it.

00:11:59.052 --> 00:12:02.055 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So how do you teach this
to someone who has anxiety,

00:12:02.055 --> 00:12:05.091 align:middle line:84%
who has fears that
are legitimate fears?

00:12:05.091 --> 00:12:10.463 align:middle line:84%
How do you teach that art of
mindfulness to someone in this--

00:12:10.463 --> 00:12:12.799 align:middle line:84%
in a place where they
are not aware of it?

00:12:12.799 --> 00:12:14.901 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: You don't teach
anyone till want to learn.

00:12:14.901 --> 00:12:15.468 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:12:15.468 --> 00:12:16.670 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: You know.

00:12:16.670 --> 00:12:19.506 align:middle line:84%
So nobody walks through
the door and gets into one

00:12:19.506 --> 00:12:21.741 align:middle line:84%
of my retreats unless
they're asking questions.

00:12:21.741 --> 00:12:24.744 align:middle line:84%
They read my book,
something bounces of the page

00:12:24.744 --> 00:12:27.981 align:middle line:84%
and they hear answers to
their own inner issues.

00:12:27.981 --> 00:12:31.818 align:middle line:84%
That book teaches people
how to learn to deal

00:12:31.818 --> 00:12:36.022 align:middle line:84%
with what their mind is creating
and what it's doing to them.

00:12:36.022 --> 00:12:37.424 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: We're going to
talk all about that, yeah.

00:12:37.424 --> 00:12:38.859 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And so you
can teach people

00:12:38.859 --> 00:12:41.027 align:middle line:84%
but it's not an intellectual
process.

00:12:41.027 --> 00:12:42.963 align:middle line:84%
When you recognize what
you're doing to yourself

00:12:42.963 --> 00:12:45.665 align:middle line:84%
with a thought is because
you feel that in your body

00:12:45.665 --> 00:12:48.235 align:middle line:84%
and the problem with
most western people

00:12:48.235 --> 00:12:50.804 align:middle line:84%
or most modern people is
we're never in our bodies.

00:12:50.804 --> 00:12:52.138 align:middle line:90%
We train our body.

00:12:52.138 --> 00:12:53.540 align:middle line:90%
We run. We jog.

00:12:53.540 --> 00:12:54.207 align:middle line:90%
We train it.

00:12:54.207 --> 00:12:55.475 align:middle line:90%
But we're not in it.

00:12:55.475 --> 00:12:56.676 align:middle line:84%
You can be a professional
athlete

00:12:56.676 --> 00:13:00.146 align:middle line:84%
and have no idea what it
means to be in your body.

00:13:00.146 --> 00:13:02.349 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: I try to explain
that to my daughter a lot

00:13:02.349 --> 00:13:04.618 align:middle line:84%
when she's bumping into
things and she has no idea--

00:13:04.618 --> 00:13:06.853 align:middle line:84%
and I don't know how to tell
her, you're not in your body.

00:13:06.853 --> 00:13:07.921 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: When you're in your body,

00:13:07.921 --> 00:13:09.923 align:middle line:84%
you recognize what a
thought does to you.

00:13:09.923 --> 00:13:11.558 align:middle line:84%
When you're in your
body, you recognize one

00:13:11.558 --> 00:13:12.726 align:middle line:90%
of the weather of feeling.

00:13:12.726 --> 00:13:14.995 align:middle line:84%
The weather is beautiful
outside today

00:13:14.995 --> 00:13:16.897 align:middle line:84%
that we're just new
here, you know.

00:13:16.897 --> 00:13:17.964 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:13:17.964 --> 00:13:19.399 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: But what if
it's a storm tomorrow?

00:13:19.399 --> 00:13:21.368 align:middle line:84%
Feeling is as mode
of consciousness

00:13:21.368 --> 00:13:22.636 align:middle line:90%
and it changes all the time.

00:13:22.636 --> 00:13:24.938 align:middle line:84%
But if it throws, if
it's a scary feeling,

00:13:24.938 --> 00:13:27.507 align:middle line:84%
or threatening feeling,
it throws in thought.

00:13:27.507 --> 00:13:30.143 align:middle line:84%
Those thoughts will
arose emotions like anger

00:13:30.143 --> 00:13:32.612 align:middle line:90%
or bitterness or even fear.

00:13:32.612 --> 00:13:34.180 align:middle line:90%
You said normal fear.

00:13:34.180 --> 00:13:37.050 align:middle line:84%
It's very, very little truly
normal fear in the world.

00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:39.286 align:middle line:90%
It's almost all mind made.

00:13:39.286 --> 00:13:40.520 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: True, yes.

00:13:40.520 --> 00:13:43.423 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: You stop the thoughts
when you have real fear,

00:13:43.423 --> 00:13:47.294 align:middle line:84%
then a healthy relationship
to that is vulnerability.

00:13:47.294 --> 00:13:49.396 align:middle line:84%
And most people are
working too much takes--

00:13:49.396 --> 00:13:51.865 align:middle line:84%
avoid vulnerability or
they're buying things

00:13:51.865 --> 00:13:53.500 align:middle line:90%
to avoid vulnerability.

00:13:53.500 --> 00:13:56.136 align:middle line:84%
They're reshaping their
faces and their bodies

00:13:56.136 --> 00:13:57.304 align:middle line:90%
to avoid vulnerability.

00:13:57.304 --> 00:14:00.307 align:middle line:84%
They're-- You know,
they're running away

00:14:00.307 --> 00:14:02.676 align:middle line:84%
from through what they
imagine would be success.

00:14:02.676 --> 00:14:05.011 align:middle line:84%
But the-- Once you
lose vulnerability

00:14:05.011 --> 00:14:08.114 align:middle line:84%
in a relationship,
you lose love.

00:14:08.114 --> 00:14:10.917 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: In this situation,
as my father who is afraid

00:14:10.917 --> 00:14:15.455 align:middle line:84%
of his memory slipping and
he goes into so much fear

00:14:15.455 --> 00:14:18.625 align:middle line:84%
when he forgets something that
it almost blocks him completely

00:14:18.625 --> 00:14:20.860 align:middle line:84%
from being able to
ever remember it.

00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:23.196 align:middle line:84%
And I was trying to
explain to him to relax

00:14:23.196 --> 00:14:26.766 align:middle line:84%
and he's an ex-medical
doctor like you are, retired.

00:14:26.766 --> 00:14:29.936 align:middle line:90%
And to teach him mindfulness,

00:14:29.936 --> 00:14:32.672 align:middle line:84%
I always having hard
time explaining it.

00:14:32.672 --> 00:14:34.407 align:middle line:84%
So today, what we're
doing in the show is

00:14:34.407 --> 00:14:36.876 align:middle line:84%
that there are certain
elements that you've describe

00:14:36.876 --> 00:14:40.280 align:middle line:84%
in the course of this
experience that we're going

00:14:40.280 --> 00:14:42.115 align:middle line:84%
to be able teach people
that you are going

00:14:42.115 --> 00:14:43.984 align:middle line:90%
to be able to teach people.

00:14:43.984 --> 00:14:45.385 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:14:45.385 --> 00:14:48.254 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And this is through the
first element is understanding

00:14:48.254 --> 00:14:50.323 align:middle line:90%
where and when to begin.

00:14:50.323 --> 00:14:54.227 align:middle line:84%
So where and how and when could
I tell my father to begin?

00:14:54.227 --> 00:14:57.497 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Well, the only time
you could begin is now,

00:14:57.497 --> 00:14:59.632 align:middle line:90%
this moment, right?

00:14:59.632 --> 00:15:01.801 align:middle line:84%
Because if you--
where would you begin?

00:15:01.801 --> 00:15:04.904 align:middle line:84%
Would you begin with his
medical training that tells him

00:15:04.904 --> 00:15:07.440 align:middle line:84%
that this lapses of memory
could be an indication

00:15:07.440 --> 00:15:10.176 align:middle line:84%
of early onset dementia,
early onset Alzheimer's.

00:15:10.176 --> 00:15:11.511 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:15:11.511 --> 00:15:14.848 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: You know, he has to
begin now and you have to begin.

00:15:14.848 --> 00:15:17.283 align:middle line:84%
We all have to start now
'cause that's all we have.

00:15:17.283 --> 00:15:19.819 align:middle line:84%
So what we have in the
present moment is awareness.

00:15:19.819 --> 00:15:21.121 align:middle line:90%
You can be aware.

00:15:21.121 --> 00:15:24.591 align:middle line:84%
I'm now telling myself a
story that I'm losing my mind.

00:15:24.591 --> 00:15:27.927 align:middle line:84%
And what's doing to me in
this moment is actually making

00:15:27.927 --> 00:15:28.828 align:middle line:90%
me fearful.

00:15:28.828 --> 00:15:30.830 align:middle line:90%
It's actually making me anxious.

00:15:30.830 --> 00:15:33.400 align:middle line:84%
So I'm poisoning myself
with neurotransmitters

00:15:33.400 --> 00:15:37.070 align:middle line:84%
that are constricting my
heart, tightening my breathing,

00:15:37.070 --> 00:15:41.273 align:middle line:84%
agitating me in this
moment because I'm starting

00:15:41.273 --> 00:15:45.011 align:middle line:84%
from a memory that was taught
to me, medical education,

00:15:45.011 --> 00:15:46.713 align:middle line:90%
and I'm jumping into the future.

00:15:46.713 --> 00:15:47.213 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:15:47.213 --> 00:15:47.914 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: OK.

00:15:47.914 --> 00:15:49.049 align:middle line:90%
He starts with the past.

00:15:49.049 --> 00:15:49.983 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:15:49.983 --> 00:15:51.217 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: He wasn't
like this before.

00:15:51.217 --> 00:15:52.018 align:middle line:90%
He's read this stuff.

00:15:52.018 --> 00:15:53.053 align:middle line:90%
He studied this stuff.

00:15:53.053 --> 00:15:54.654 align:middle line:84%
Oh, now, oh, my God,
it's Alzheimer's.

00:15:54.654 --> 00:15:56.022 align:middle line:90%
He jumps to the future.

00:15:56.022 --> 00:15:57.457 align:middle line:84%
It's going to get
worse [inaudible].

00:15:57.457 --> 00:16:00.093 align:middle line:84%
And he's terrifying
himself with the future.

00:16:00.093 --> 00:16:03.530 align:middle line:84%
He's remembering a past
that he thinks was healthy

00:16:03.530 --> 00:16:05.598 align:middle line:84%
but [inaudible] information
that's he's using now

00:16:05.598 --> 00:16:07.100 align:middle line:90%
to poison the present moment.

00:16:07.100 --> 00:16:09.369 align:middle line:84%
And everybody is doing
that all the time.

00:16:09.369 --> 00:16:11.004 align:middle line:90%
It's not the situation.

00:16:11.004 --> 00:16:12.539 align:middle line:90%
It's the story you tell yourself

00:16:12.539 --> 00:16:15.942 align:middle line:84%
about the situation
that's so disruptive.

00:16:15.942 --> 00:16:18.378 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: What if in that moment
somebody is saying something

00:16:18.378 --> 00:16:20.747 align:middle line:84%
that's upsetting you,
or criticizing you,

00:16:20.747 --> 00:16:23.483 align:middle line:84%
or saying something, is it--
again, even if that's happening

00:16:23.483 --> 00:16:26.319 align:middle line:84%
in that moment, is it the story
that you're telling yourself

00:16:26.319 --> 00:16:29.022 align:middle line:90%
about that conversation?

00:16:29.022 --> 00:16:32.725 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: My life partner and
I, we practice what we call--

00:16:32.725 --> 00:16:34.360 align:middle line:84%
what I call consecrated
conversation,

00:16:34.360 --> 00:16:35.862 align:middle line:90%
which we teach to people.

00:16:35.862 --> 00:16:39.532 align:middle line:84%
If she starts saying something
to me that upsets me--

00:16:39.532 --> 00:16:40.667 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:16:40.667 --> 00:16:42.268 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: I know, A, I'm
listening with my head.

00:16:42.268 --> 00:16:43.336 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:16:43.336 --> 00:16:44.437 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: I'm listening
with my psychology,

00:16:44.437 --> 00:16:46.406 align:middle line:84%
what I want to have
come from her.

00:16:46.406 --> 00:16:50.877 align:middle line:84%
So immediately, I put my
ears, my listening in my heart

00:16:50.877 --> 00:16:53.213 align:middle line:84%
and I just get bigger
and bigger and bigger

00:16:53.213 --> 00:16:55.515 align:middle line:90%
until I can really hear her.

00:16:55.515 --> 00:16:57.417 align:middle line:90%
I want to hear her.

00:16:57.417 --> 00:16:59.552 align:middle line:84%
I want her to show
me her reality.

00:16:59.552 --> 00:17:01.287 align:middle line:90%
I want to feel her reality.

00:17:01.287 --> 00:17:02.622 align:middle line:90%
I don't know want to defend.

00:17:02.622 --> 00:17:06.225 align:middle line:84%
I want her to penetrate me
so that I can really know her

00:17:06.225 --> 00:17:08.027 align:middle line:84%
and that creates a
field of connection

00:17:08.027 --> 00:17:09.963 align:middle line:90%
where she's safe to be her.

00:17:09.963 --> 00:17:11.231 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:17:11.231 --> 00:17:13.433 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So the point is people
are constantly reacting

00:17:13.433 --> 00:17:16.668 align:middle line:84%
to each other but not because
of what the other person does,

00:17:16.668 --> 00:17:18.871 align:middle line:84%
but because of the
story they themselves.

00:17:18.871 --> 00:17:20.039 align:middle line:90%
"You don't care about me."

00:17:20.039 --> 00:17:21.140 align:middle line:90%
"You don't love me."

00:17:21.140 --> 00:17:22.774 align:middle line:90%
"I'm not important to you."

00:17:22.774 --> 00:17:26.412 align:middle line:84%
And every one of those thoughts
is like a small dose of poison

00:17:26.412 --> 00:17:29.949 align:middle line:84%
and they happen all day
long hundreds a day.

00:17:29.949 --> 00:17:34.320 align:middle line:84%
And unless you wake up and
start right now and realize

00:17:34.320 --> 00:17:38.224 align:middle line:84%
that was a thought that poisoned
me now is not actually--

00:17:38.224 --> 00:17:41.594 align:middle line:84%
the only the truth of a thought
like that or the only truth

00:17:41.594 --> 00:17:45.231 align:middle line:84%
of any belief whatsoever,
religious, political,

00:17:45.231 --> 00:17:48.868 align:middle line:84%
economics is what it
makes you feel how to--

00:17:48.868 --> 00:17:52.872 align:middle line:84%
what arouses in you
and how you behave.

00:17:52.872 --> 00:17:53.907 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: So in--

00:17:53.907 --> 00:17:54.908 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: That's the
truth of a thought.

00:17:54.908 --> 00:17:55.708 align:middle line:84%
The beliefs themselves,
there's no way

00:17:55.708 --> 00:17:57.076 align:middle line:90%
to prove that they're true.

00:17:57.076 --> 00:18:00.246 align:middle line:84%
So if you say, "You don't
care about me," the truth

00:18:00.246 --> 00:18:02.782 align:middle line:84%
of that is it makes you
angry or it makes you sad.

00:18:02.782 --> 00:18:03.716 align:middle line:90%
And then you close down.

00:18:03.716 --> 00:18:04.584 align:middle line:90%
That's you're behavior.

00:18:04.584 --> 00:18:05.418 align:middle line:90%
Or you get aggressive.

00:18:05.418 --> 00:18:06.386 align:middle line:90%
That's your behavior.

00:18:06.386 --> 00:18:07.787 align:middle line:90%
That's the truth.

00:18:07.787 --> 00:18:10.890 align:middle line:84%
There is no other truth to
you don't care about me.

00:18:10.890 --> 00:18:12.692 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: What about an
abusive relationship

00:18:12.692 --> 00:18:14.594 align:middle line:84%
where the abuse is
still occurring?

00:18:14.594 --> 00:18:16.062 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Now, abuse is different.

00:18:16.062 --> 00:18:16.563 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:18:16.563 --> 00:18:17.263 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: OK.

00:18:17.263 --> 00:18:18.798 align:middle line:90%
Abuse is the physical--

00:18:18.798 --> 00:18:20.967 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Or emotional.

00:18:20.967 --> 00:18:21.601 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: No.

00:18:21.601 --> 00:18:22.602 align:middle line:90%
You know what?

00:18:22.602 --> 00:18:24.337 align:middle line:90%
Nobody can emotionally hurt you.

00:18:24.337 --> 00:18:27.173 align:middle line:84%
It's the story you tell yourself
about what they say to you.

00:18:27.173 --> 00:18:30.076 align:middle line:84%
And if you put those
stories aside

00:18:30.076 --> 00:18:33.680 align:middle line:84%
and that relationship is
still so unpleasant to be in,

00:18:33.680 --> 00:18:37.450 align:middle line:84%
then you move on because there's
a-- it-- life is too precious.

00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:38.818 align:middle line:90%
Your body is a temple.

00:18:38.818 --> 00:18:41.421 align:middle line:84%
It should not be constantly
having to make space

00:18:41.421 --> 00:18:44.858 align:middle line:84%
for someone who's
posses by their stories.

00:18:44.858 --> 00:18:48.127 align:middle line:84%
It has to be aggressive or
has to be attacking or it has

00:18:48.127 --> 00:18:51.431 align:middle line:84%
to be dismissive,
you get up and go.

00:18:51.431 --> 00:18:52.899 align:middle line:84%
Or you say, "Look,
I want to work

00:18:52.899 --> 00:18:55.435 align:middle line:84%
on this relationship
'cause there's a--

00:18:55.435 --> 00:18:57.637 align:middle line:84%
you whiz [phonetic] to have
an incredibly deep connection

00:18:57.637 --> 00:18:58.404 align:middle line:90%
and we've lost it.

00:18:58.404 --> 00:18:59.606 align:middle line:90%
I want to work on it."

00:18:59.606 --> 00:19:01.908 align:middle line:84%
And if the other person
says "Yes," then you start

00:19:01.908 --> 00:19:05.111 align:middle line:84%
down the path of really
working relationship

00:19:05.111 --> 00:19:06.512 align:middle line:90%
which requires presence,

00:19:06.512 --> 00:19:10.083 align:middle line:84%
it requires just the way
I describe how I listen

00:19:10.083 --> 00:19:13.519 align:middle line:84%
in my relationship and
in all my relationships

00:19:13.519 --> 00:19:16.089 align:middle line:84%
and that requires
practice everyday.

00:19:16.089 --> 00:19:17.323 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: It would also--

00:19:17.323 --> 00:19:19.859 align:middle line:84%
that expansiveness would
also call to the attention.

00:19:19.859 --> 00:19:23.062 align:middle line:84%
If there is something
innately wrong and then to have

00:19:23.062 --> 00:19:26.866 align:middle line:84%
as enough self-worth and
self-love to exit out of

00:19:26.866 --> 00:19:29.102 align:middle line:84%
that situation if
it's truly bad.

00:19:29.102 --> 00:19:30.069 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Sure.

00:19:30.069 --> 00:19:31.170 align:middle line:84%
And if it's physical
abuse, get out.

00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:32.005 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Of course.

00:19:32.005 --> 00:19:34.140 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: That-- You know, I'm not

00:19:34.140 --> 00:19:36.409 align:middle line:84%
in any way condoning
physical abuse,

00:19:36.409 --> 00:19:39.012 align:middle line:84%
I don't condone emotional
attack either.

00:19:39.012 --> 00:19:43.449 align:middle line:84%
But I have to tell you, first
find out what inside of you has

00:19:43.449 --> 00:19:47.920 align:middle line:84%
to tell yourself a judgmental
or defensive or attacking story

00:19:47.920 --> 00:19:50.490 align:middle line:84%
about your partner,
stop that in yourself

00:19:50.490 --> 00:19:52.659 align:middle line:84%
and then you may find
there's no actual connect

00:19:52.659 --> 00:19:54.927 align:middle line:84%
between you anymore
and you can walk out.

00:19:54.927 --> 00:19:57.430 align:middle line:84%
But what's going on
really if people stay

00:19:57.430 --> 00:19:58.798 align:middle line:90%
in an abusive relationship,

00:19:58.798 --> 00:20:00.633 align:middle line:84%
emotionally abusive
relationship,

00:20:00.633 --> 00:20:02.635 align:middle line:84%
not a physical abusive
relationship,

00:20:02.635 --> 00:20:04.570 align:middle line:90%
is that they are afraid.

00:20:04.570 --> 00:20:06.606 align:middle line:90%
They are afraid of being alone.

00:20:06.606 --> 00:20:08.474 align:middle line:90%
They're afraid of abandonment.

00:20:08.474 --> 00:20:11.244 align:middle line:84%
They're afraid of--
so they haven't got--

00:20:11.244 --> 00:20:14.280 align:middle line:84%
they haven't developed
in the now

00:20:14.280 --> 00:20:16.182 align:middle line:84%
because that's the
only thing that exists.

00:20:16.182 --> 00:20:19.118 align:middle line:84%
They haven't developed
the relationship to fear.

00:20:19.118 --> 00:20:21.020 align:middle line:84%
And for the vast
majority of people,

00:20:21.020 --> 00:20:22.989 align:middle line:84%
fear is the god ruling
their lives.

00:20:22.989 --> 00:20:24.457 align:middle line:90%
It drives consumers.

00:20:24.457 --> 00:20:27.360 align:middle line:90%
It drives the cosmetic world.

00:20:27.360 --> 00:20:29.028 align:middle line:90%
It drives cosmetic surgery.

00:20:29.028 --> 00:20:32.765 align:middle line:84%
It drives-- 'Cause, you
know, basically materialism,

00:20:32.765 --> 00:20:35.068 align:middle line:84%
we imagine that we
can find happiness

00:20:35.068 --> 00:20:38.237 align:middle line:84%
from something outside,
because we don't how to make--

00:20:38.237 --> 00:20:42.275 align:middle line:84%
a big enough space inside of
us in this moment for fear

00:20:42.275 --> 00:20:45.912 align:middle line:84%
for sensations, for fear
has-- is one sensation,

00:20:45.912 --> 00:20:49.882 align:middle line:84%
a different intensities
with thousands of names.

00:20:49.882 --> 00:20:53.486 align:middle line:84%
You know, we're in 22nd floors,
"Oh my God, fear of heights."

00:20:53.486 --> 00:20:54.520 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:20:54.520 --> 00:20:55.922 align:middle line:84%
OK, so how do you
make space for fear?

00:20:55.922 --> 00:20:57.123 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: That's a practice.

00:20:57.123 --> 00:20:59.592 align:middle line:84%
You realized that
you'll never be safe,

00:20:59.592 --> 00:21:02.528 align:middle line:84%
that when you make space
for fear, you're vulnerable.

00:21:02.528 --> 00:21:04.831 align:middle line:84%
To be vulnerable in
a relationship means,

00:21:04.831 --> 00:21:08.134 align:middle line:84%
I say to you what I really
feel and it can be almost

00:21:08.134 --> 00:21:10.603 align:middle line:84%
like I'm going to die if I
tell you what I really feel,

00:21:10.603 --> 00:21:11.137 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:21:11.137 --> 00:21:12.538 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:21:12.538 --> 00:21:14.073 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: This-- To overcome the
fact that you might reject me,

00:21:14.073 --> 00:21:16.542 align:middle line:84%
or you might think I'm weak
or you might think needy--

00:21:16.542 --> 00:21:17.377 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:21:17.377 --> 00:21:18.444 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: -- you know what I mean?

00:21:18.444 --> 00:21:20.279 align:middle line:84%
You have to be willing
to be vulnerable.

00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:21.447 align:middle line:90%
And what do we do?

00:21:21.447 --> 00:21:23.316 align:middle line:84%
We get busy to not
be vulnerable.

00:21:23.316 --> 00:21:24.951 align:middle line:84%
We work too much to
not be vulnerable.

00:21:24.951 --> 00:21:25.785 align:middle line:90%
We drink--

00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:26.486 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Protect yourselves, yes.

00:21:26.486 --> 00:21:27.053 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: -- in every way--

00:21:27.053 --> 00:21:28.021 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:21:28.021 --> 00:21:29.589 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: -- activity,
drugs, booze,

00:21:29.589 --> 00:21:33.326 align:middle line:84%
things to not be vulnerable and
once the vulnerability is gone

00:21:33.326 --> 00:21:35.027 align:middle line:90%
as I think I said before so--

00:21:35.027 --> 00:21:37.363 align:middle line:84%
or maybe when we were
talking before the show,

00:21:37.363 --> 00:21:39.432 align:middle line:90%
then the love is gone.

00:21:39.432 --> 00:21:42.902 align:middle line:84%
Without vulnerability people
can't connect and I was

00:21:42.902 --> 00:21:45.004 align:middle line:90%
so vulnerable in that awakening.

00:21:45.004 --> 00:21:47.206 align:middle line:90%
It just took me apart.

00:21:47.206 --> 00:21:48.341 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:21:48.341 --> 00:21:49.609 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And then when the
black butterfly landed

00:21:49.609 --> 00:21:51.878 align:middle line:84%
for a little while I knew
what it was like to be one

00:21:51.878 --> 00:21:53.613 align:middle line:90%
with everything, you know.

00:21:53.613 --> 00:21:56.149 align:middle line:84%
I knew what supernal peacement,
I knew what the peace,

00:21:56.149 --> 00:21:59.118 align:middle line:84%
I knew what the peace that
passive understanding means

00:21:59.118 --> 00:22:00.486 align:middle line:90%
when you read it in scripture.

00:22:00.486 --> 00:22:01.687 align:middle line:90%
I knew it.

00:22:01.687 --> 00:22:04.891 align:middle line:84%
And I knew what it
meant to be born again

00:22:04.891 --> 00:22:06.926 align:middle line:84%
in a very true sense
of the world.

00:22:06.926 --> 00:22:07.727 align:middle line:90%
We're not--

00:22:07.727 --> 00:22:08.861 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Unfair but--

00:22:08.861 --> 00:22:11.030 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: -- not adapting a
religious belief system

00:22:11.030 --> 00:22:14.500 align:middle line:84%
because beliefs are again just
stories you tell yourself whose

00:22:14.500 --> 00:22:16.402 align:middle line:84%
truth is that it makes
you feel a certain way

00:22:16.402 --> 00:22:18.638 align:middle line:84%
or gives you a community
to join with

00:22:18.638 --> 00:22:21.207 align:middle line:90%
and determines your behavior.

00:22:21.207 --> 00:22:25.111 align:middle line:84%
But real faith has
no beliefs in at all.

00:22:25.111 --> 00:22:28.281 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: That makes perfect sense,
now that you explain like that.

00:22:28.281 --> 00:22:30.249 align:middle line:90%
So, I'm learning vulnerability,

00:22:30.249 --> 00:22:33.085 align:middle line:84%
I'm learning space
for vulnerability.

00:22:33.085 --> 00:22:36.222 align:middle line:84%
So element one was understanding
where and when to begin.

00:22:36.222 --> 00:22:38.825 align:middle line:84%
Element two is live more
consistently in the now,

00:22:38.825 --> 00:22:41.160 align:middle line:84%
which we just talked
about and that brings is

00:22:41.160 --> 00:22:42.962 align:middle line:90%
to "The Mandala of Being".

00:22:42.962 --> 00:22:44.297 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: OK.

00:22:44.297 --> 00:22:47.300 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And so this diagram
that you shared with us talks

00:22:47.300 --> 00:22:49.368 align:middle line:84%
about how or either
in the present or--

00:22:49.368 --> 00:22:51.537 align:middle line:84%
no, we're either in the
past or in the future.

00:22:51.537 --> 00:22:52.638 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: So my question

00:22:52.638 --> 00:22:55.975 align:middle line:84%
to the viewer is how
many nows do you see?

00:22:55.975 --> 00:22:57.043 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: One?

00:22:57.043 --> 00:22:58.377 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: OK that's
what everybody says.

00:22:58.377 --> 00:22:59.212 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:22:59.212 --> 00:23:01.113 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Actually there's five.

00:23:01.113 --> 00:23:03.950 align:middle line:84%
There's the now at the
center, which is the now

00:23:03.950 --> 00:23:06.385 align:middle line:84%
of the professional athlete
whose mind disappears

00:23:06.385 --> 00:23:07.753 align:middle line:90%
in to the perfect action.

