>> RM: The guy on the surfboard,
the women-- the Olympic skier,

00:23:10.990 --> 00:23:12.892 align:middle line:84%
any skier that when
you're in flow.

00:23:12.892 --> 00:23:14.026 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Flow.

00:23:14.026 --> 00:23:15.828 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Or a person who's
practice contemplation

00:23:15.828 --> 00:23:19.465 align:middle line:84%
and deep meditation, that's
the now not condition,

00:23:19.465 --> 00:23:21.834 align:middle line:84%
not effective, not
influenced, not determined

00:23:21.834 --> 00:23:23.769 align:middle line:90%
by any form of thought.

00:23:23.769 --> 00:23:25.204 align:middle line:90%
And it's the now of being--

00:23:25.204 --> 00:23:27.707 align:middle line:84%
without resistance
to what you feel.

00:23:27.707 --> 00:23:31.143 align:middle line:84%
The other four nows,
the one that says me,

00:23:31.143 --> 00:23:35.081 align:middle line:84%
that's the now created in this
moment when you judge yourself.

00:23:35.081 --> 00:23:37.617 align:middle line:84%
And you judge yourself to be
smarter and to know what needs

00:23:37.617 --> 00:23:41.654 align:middle line:84%
to be done, so you make yourself
special but you puff up and big,

00:23:41.654 --> 00:23:42.889 align:middle line:90%
grandiose, specialness.

00:23:42.889 --> 00:23:45.124 align:middle line:84%
Or you judge yourself to
be not so good, you know,

00:23:45.124 --> 00:23:48.261 align:middle line:84%
and not as attractive and,
you know, not a smart,

00:23:48.261 --> 00:23:50.696 align:middle line:84%
and so you make yourself
special but its depressive.

00:23:50.696 --> 00:23:54.100 align:middle line:84%
There's a now when you
tell-- judge other people.

00:23:54.100 --> 00:23:56.836 align:middle line:84%
You either make them bigger,
you make them smaller it leads

00:23:56.836 --> 00:24:01.674 align:middle line:84%
to envy, or adoration, or
resentment, or bitterness,

00:24:01.674 --> 00:24:03.109 align:middle line:90%
those are the 'you' stories.

00:24:03.109 --> 00:24:05.478 align:middle line:84%
So when you believe the
judgment of another,

00:24:05.478 --> 00:24:08.948 align:middle line:84%
or judgment of your situation,
or judgment of your career,

00:24:08.948 --> 00:24:12.251 align:middle line:84%
you're poisoning yourself at
those judgment but they're not--

00:24:12.251 --> 00:24:15.288 align:middle line:84%
so you're in the now
created by the emotion,

00:24:15.288 --> 00:24:17.290 align:middle line:90%
the arousal of those stories.

00:24:17.290 --> 00:24:22.228 align:middle line:84%
Same thing with the past,
it's gone, most memory comes

00:24:22.228 --> 00:24:25.598 align:middle line:84%
from the-- is activated
in the same part

00:24:25.598 --> 00:24:28.334 align:middle line:84%
of the brain that's
has imagination.

00:24:28.334 --> 00:24:32.605 align:middle line:84%
So the actual what really memory
is, is re imagining the past.

00:24:32.605 --> 00:24:34.006 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:24:34.006 --> 00:24:35.374 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And if you depress today
you'll re-imagine the situation

00:24:35.374 --> 00:24:38.344 align:middle line:84%
with your father 20, or 30,
or 40 years ago in such a way

00:24:38.344 --> 00:24:39.579 align:middle line:90%
as to support depression.

00:24:39.579 --> 00:24:42.348 align:middle line:84%
But if you're really
feeling joyous today and full

00:24:42.348 --> 00:24:45.284 align:middle line:84%
in yourself, you'll
re-imagine the exact same memory

00:24:45.284 --> 00:24:47.820 align:middle line:90%
