to please their parents,
to please their husbands,

00:34:41.046 --> 00:34:43.849 align:middle line:84%
to please their children, to
please their boss, you know,

00:34:43.849 --> 00:34:45.316 align:middle line:90%
and they're not alive.

00:34:45.316 --> 00:34:46.718 align:middle line:84%
And one day they
wake up and say,

00:34:46.718 --> 00:34:49.588 align:middle line:84%
"Pleasing isn't a good
adaptation as an adult.

00:34:49.588 --> 00:34:52.324 align:middle line:84%
But pleasing is so good when
you are in this classroom

00:34:52.324 --> 00:34:54.560 align:middle line:84%
with a teacher who doesn't
want to struggle with you."

00:34:54.560 --> 00:34:58.063 align:middle line:84%
Whereas the rebel is a problem
and the introvert that focuses

00:34:58.063 --> 00:34:59.198 align:middle line:90%
in on the-- but that's the--

00:34:59.198 --> 00:35:00.465 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And you want to
be the good little girl.

00:35:00.465 --> 00:35:01.266 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: That's the
problem, you know.

00:35:01.266 --> 00:35:02.434 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:35:02.434 --> 00:35:04.069 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And pretty soon
we got these labels.

00:35:04.069 --> 00:35:07.439 align:middle line:84%
When in reality people--
people learn in different ways

00:35:07.439 --> 00:35:10.409 align:middle line:84%
and if there's-- we need
people to be different.

00:35:10.409 --> 00:35:13.212 align:middle line:84%
The only trouble is our
educational system is a one size

00:35:13.212 --> 00:35:15.447 align:middle line:90%
fits all and doesn't work.

00:35:15.447 --> 00:35:17.182 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And that's when you
bring in your choice of what

00:35:17.182 --> 00:35:19.818 align:middle line:84%
to be expanded about and
what to be contracted about.

00:35:19.818 --> 00:35:21.954 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Well I said
to him, be a champion

00:35:21.954 --> 00:35:23.922 align:middle line:90%
for your son, your sons.

00:35:23.922 --> 00:35:27.025 align:middle line:84%
You know, you're the one that
believes in them the most.

00:35:27.025 --> 00:35:31.697 align:middle line:84%
And whenever they do something
that you feel is a violation

00:35:31.697 --> 00:35:33.799 align:middle line:84%
of proper boundaries,
don't be worried

00:35:33.799 --> 00:35:36.935 align:middle line:84%
about whether they're ill,
show them what matters to you.

00:35:36.935 --> 00:35:40.439 align:middle line:84%
Set the-- Set the boundary and
then continue being a champion,

00:35:40.439 --> 00:35:42.307 align:middle line:84%
you don't have to
accept their behavior

00:35:42.307 --> 00:35:44.309 align:middle line:90%
without every rejecting them.

00:35:44.309 --> 00:35:45.010 align:middle line:90%
He say, this--

00:35:45.010 --> 00:35:46.612 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:35:46.612 --> 00:35:49.414 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: You-- I believe in
you in every possible way

00:35:49.414 --> 00:35:52.718 align:middle line:84%
that behavior doesn't--
doesn't work for me, you know.

00:35:52.718 --> 00:35:53.986 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: That's inclusive.

00:35:53.986 --> 00:35:59.725 align:middle line:84%
All right, so wow, element
five is effort and grace,

00:35:59.725 --> 00:36:01.226 align:middle line:90%
is there a difference?

00:36:01.226 --> 00:36:03.595 align:middle line:84%
Is-- they're the same--
Is it the same thing?

00:36:03.595 --> 00:36:06.365 align:middle line:84%
How-- What is effort
and grace mean?

00:36:06.365 --> 00:36:08.767 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Effort is you
wake up in the middle

00:36:08.767 --> 00:36:11.536 align:middle line:84%
of telling yourself a me story
that's making you depressive,

00:36:11.536 --> 00:36:12.037 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:36:12.037 --> 00:36:13.238 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:36:13.238 --> 00:36:14.473 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And you say, "I'm
going to start right now."

00:36:14.473 --> 00:36:15.807 align:middle line:90%
You wake up in the middle

00:36:15.807 --> 00:36:18.343 align:middle line:84%
of the future story that's
making you anxious and afraid

00:36:18.343 --> 00:36:21.914 align:middle line:84%
or hopeful in a way that's
actually going to 'cause you

00:36:21.914 --> 00:36:23.949 align:middle line:84%
to stay in the stock marker
much too long, you know,

00:36:23.949 --> 00:36:26.785 align:middle line:90%
that kind of foolish hope.

00:36:26.785 --> 00:36:29.254 align:middle line:84%
A person living in the present
moment never needs hope,

00:36:29.254 --> 00:36:31.490 align:middle line:84%
because they're living
with what is.

00:36:31.490 --> 00:36:33.859 align:middle line:84%
Hope is only for
people who can't stay

00:36:33.859 --> 00:36:35.060 align:middle line:90%
on the present moment.

00:36:35.060 --> 00:36:36.194 align:middle line:90%
You don't need hope.

00:36:36.194 --> 00:36:38.096 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: What about goals
in futures setting and--

00:36:38.096 --> 00:36:39.765 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So what, I
have tremendous goals.

00:36:39.765 --> 00:36:43.568 align:middle line:84%
I want to heal as many people
as I can and the moment I say

00:36:43.568 --> 00:36:46.405 align:middle line:84%
to myself I'm not doing enough
and feel what that thoughts

00:36:46.405 --> 00:36:47.906 align:middle line:90%
to me, does to me I drop it.

00:36:47.906 --> 00:36:50.275 align:middle line:84%
If I heard the thought
God wants you do to more

00:36:50.275 --> 00:36:52.911 align:middle line:84%
and it made my body even
slightly contracted,

00:36:52.911 --> 00:36:55.380 align:middle line:84%
I throw away that
God and that thought.

00:36:55.380 --> 00:36:57.849 align:middle line:84%
This temple doesn't
need that misery.

00:36:57.849 --> 00:36:59.217 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:36:59.217 --> 00:37:00.652 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: I'm not-- So that's the
practice that's the effort.

00:37:00.652 --> 00:37:03.689 align:middle line:84%
The grace is the
current you feel,

00:37:03.689 --> 00:37:06.058 align:middle line:84%
that I feel all the
time coming through me.

00:37:06.058 --> 00:37:07.092 align:middle line:90%
Not all the time.

00:37:07.092 --> 00:37:08.560 align:middle line:84%
There are certain
moments particularly

00:37:08.560 --> 00:37:09.828 align:middle line:90%
in intimate relationship

00:37:09.828 --> 00:37:13.198 align:middle line:84%
where my early childhood
staff gets triggered, but I--

00:37:13.198 --> 00:37:15.901 align:middle line:84%
I'm now know how to be a very
vulnerable in that as oppose

00:37:15.901 --> 00:37:19.171 align:middle line:84%
to close down, shutoff,
withdraw, or get aggressive.

00:37:19.171 --> 00:37:20.639 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Got it.

00:37:20.639 --> 00:37:23.308 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: So, you know,
I'm a work in progress.

00:37:23.308 --> 00:37:26.278 align:middle line:84%
The effort is how you
want to invent yourself.

00:37:26.278 --> 00:37:28.413 align:middle line:90%
The grace is that you can.

00:37:28.413 --> 00:37:31.383 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: This is an amazing
tool for going into some

00:37:31.383 --> 00:37:34.353 align:middle line:84%
of the most negative environment
and transforming yourself

00:37:34.353 --> 00:37:35.887 align:middle line:90%
within that environment.

00:37:35.887 --> 00:37:37.289 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yeah.

00:37:37.289 --> 00:37:38.190 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And then transforming the
environment and those that are

00:37:38.190 --> 00:37:41.326 align:middle line:90%
around you in response to that.

00:37:41.326 --> 00:37:43.962 align:middle line:90%
If you choose to invent yourself

00:37:43.962 --> 00:37:46.732 align:middle line:84%
by doing what this book
teaches people how to do--

00:37:46.732 --> 00:37:47.833 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Oh gosh, we
haven't even talked

00:37:47.833 --> 00:37:50.068 align:middle line:84%
about the self healing
aspects of all this.

00:37:50.068 --> 00:37:51.003 align:middle line:90%
Well here is a technique.

00:37:51.003 --> 00:37:52.804 align:middle line:84%
I want you to take
a look at of--

00:37:52.804 --> 00:37:54.439 align:middle line:90%
of what Richard talks about.

00:37:54.439 --> 00:37:58.076 align:middle line:84%
How do you use breath to get to
this transformative experience?

00:37:58.076 --> 00:37:59.211 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:37:59.211 --> 00:38:02.347 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: It's so easy to
get caught in our heads,

00:38:02.347 --> 00:38:03.849 align:middle line:84%
and one of the most
important things

00:38:03.849 --> 00:38:07.986 align:middle line:84%
that we can learn is how very
quickly to center ourselves.

00:38:07.986 --> 00:38:12.824 align:middle line:84%
So here's one way
that you can practice.

00:38:12.824 --> 00:38:13.925 align:middle line:90%
The nature of consciousness

00:38:13.925 --> 00:38:16.995 align:middle line:84%
in the present moment
is very different

00:38:16.995 --> 00:38:18.630 align:middle line:90%
than what we learn in school.

00:38:18.630 --> 00:38:20.932 align:middle line:84%
In school we focus
and we narrow.

00:38:20.932 --> 00:38:23.435 align:middle line:84%
The consciousness in the
present moment when you're

00:38:23.435 --> 00:38:25.370 align:middle line:84%
in deep meditation,
when you're surfing,

00:38:25.370 --> 00:38:28.774 align:middle line:84%
when you're skiing is
an extraordinary sense

00:38:28.774 --> 00:38:33.879 align:middle line:84%
of the vividness of all your
perceptions and expansiveness.

00:38:33.879 --> 00:38:37.349 align:middle line:84%
So all you have to
do is shift from time

00:38:37.349 --> 00:38:38.717 align:middle line:90%
to time to your breathing.

00:38:38.717 --> 00:38:43.922 align:middle line:84%
Focus for example on this
sensation of the air moving

00:38:43.922 --> 00:38:49.828 align:middle line:84%
through your nostrils, it's
very easy sensation to find,

00:38:49.828 --> 00:38:53.265 align:middle line:84%
you can have your eye open,
you can have your eyes closed.

00:38:54.499 --> 00:38:58.403 align:middle line:84%
Bring that sensation
into real vividness.

00:38:58.403 --> 00:39:00.972 align:middle line:84%
If you have to close your eyes
in order to concentrate on it

00:39:00.972 --> 00:39:05.143 align:middle line:84%
for a moment or two for a
few breaths, close your eyes.

00:39:05.143 --> 00:39:07.813 align:middle line:84%
But in daily life we want
to be able to be centered

00:39:07.813 --> 00:39:09.214 align:middle line:90%
and have our eye open.

00:39:09.214 --> 00:39:15.554 align:middle line:84%
So if your eyes open sensing the
breath moving through your nose,

00:39:15.554 --> 00:39:19.357 align:middle line:84%
aware of the light around
you, the sounds around you,

00:39:19.357 --> 00:39:24.129 align:middle line:84%
all your perceptions vivid,
simultaneously imagine

00:39:24.129 --> 00:39:27.365 align:middle line:84%
that your mind is
limitless like space.

00:39:27.365 --> 00:39:31.903 align:middle line:84%
In fact the notion of the
universe conveys a sense

00:39:31.903 --> 00:39:36.842 align:middle line:84%
of spacial vastness that the
mind itself is the vastness

00:39:36.842 --> 00:39:40.178 align:middle line:84%
in which the concept of
the universe is present.

00:39:40.178 --> 00:39:45.650 align:middle line:84%
So let yourself get
spacious, feel your body and

00:39:45.650 --> 00:39:49.888 align:middle line:84%
yet keep the sensation of
your breath truly vivid,

00:39:49.888 --> 00:39:51.957 align:middle line:90%
very precise.

00:39:51.957 --> 00:39:56.061 align:middle line:84%
Become aware of the space
around you, realize it's now,

00:39:56.061 --> 00:40:01.500 align:middle line:84%
everywhere in the universe right
in this moment, always now.

00:40:01.500 --> 00:40:04.636 align:middle line:90%
The mind in that sense limitless

00:40:04.636 --> 00:40:11.276 align:middle line:84%
and there is the very vivid
perception of your breath,

00:40:11.276 --> 00:40:15.947 align:middle line:84%
the light, the colors, the
sounds, sensations in your body,

00:40:15.947 --> 00:40:18.150 align:middle line:90%
and have five breaths.

00:40:18.150 --> 00:40:27.225 align:middle line:90%
[ Pause ]

00:40:36.968 --> 00:40:40.505 align:middle line:90%
Focused and spacious.

00:40:40.505 --> 00:40:44.109 align:middle line:84%
Precise awareness of your
whole body, of your breathing

00:40:44.109 --> 00:40:49.748 align:middle line:84%
and sense that mind in the
largest sense is limitless.

00:40:49.748 --> 00:40:53.184 align:middle line:84%
So if we were scientist, you'd
focus on what you're studying,

00:40:53.184 --> 00:40:57.522 align:middle line:84%
but you wouldn't lose the
sense of a wholistic system,

00:40:57.522 --> 00:40:59.791 align:middle line:84%
everything connected to
every thing else perspective

00:40:59.791 --> 00:41:01.059 align:middle line:90%
which is what is lost.

00:41:01.059 --> 00:41:06.031 align:middle line:84%
So just become aware
of five breaths.

00:41:06.031 --> 00:41:09.301 align:middle line:84%
Anytime you find yourself
agitated, hurrying,

00:41:09.301 --> 00:41:11.870 align:middle line:84%
starting to get caught
in emotions,

00:41:11.870 --> 00:41:13.438 align:middle line:90%
come back to the present moment.

00:41:13.438 --> 00:41:21.079 align:middle line:84%
Five focus breaths with a
spacious mind precise awareness

00:41:21.079 --> 00:41:25.684 align:middle line:84%
of your breathing, your
senses all attuned to anything

00:41:25.684 --> 00:41:30.221 align:middle line:84%
and everything, in
the sense, wow,

00:41:30.221 --> 00:41:34.059 align:middle line:90%
the mind extends limitlessly.

00:41:34.059 --> 00:41:36.228 align:middle line:90%
Five more breaths.

00:41:36.228 --> 00:41:45.303 align:middle line:90%
[ Pause ]

00:41:54.145 --> 00:41:56.715 align:middle line:84%
Most people aren't going to stop
to meditate for half an hour

00:41:56.715 --> 00:42:00.018 align:middle line:84%
or 20 minutes or 40 minutes
or an hour in the morning,

00:42:00.018 --> 00:42:03.955 align:middle line:84%
but if you do these practice
five breaths, allowing yourself

00:42:03.955 --> 00:42:10.328 align:middle line:84%
to become so precisely focused
and vast, open at the same time,

00:42:10.328 --> 00:42:13.665 align:middle line:84%
that will 'cause your
arousal level, the stimulation

00:42:13.665 --> 00:42:16.501 align:middle line:84%
of your thoughts, the emotions
they generate will come

00:42:16.501 --> 00:42:17.902 align:middle line:90%
down just a little bit.

00:42:17.902 --> 00:42:20.372 align:middle line:84%
And if 20 minutes later you do
five more breaths, it will come

00:42:20.372 --> 00:42:21.873 align:middle line:90%
down again a little bit.

00:42:21.873 --> 00:42:24.542 align:middle line:84%
And if through the day
five breaths takes what?

00:42:24.542 --> 00:42:26.011 align:middle line:90%
20 seconds?

00:42:26.011 --> 00:42:27.312 align:middle line:90%
30 seconds?

00:42:27.312 --> 00:42:31.316 align:middle line:84%
So through the day if you--
if you did this 20 times,

00:42:31.316 --> 00:42:34.853 align:middle line:84%
you would be spending five,
six, seven minutes at most

00:42:34.853 --> 00:42:37.288 align:middle line:84%
and it will really
help you center.

00:42:37.288 --> 00:42:43.361 align:middle line:84%
So take hold of this
practice and make it yours.

00:42:43.361 --> 00:42:47.499 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: How do you use that
experience of breath work

00:42:47.499 --> 00:42:50.568 align:middle line:84%
in something like a traffic
jam that we're looking

00:42:50.568 --> 00:42:52.270 align:middle line:84%
at outside the window,
there's obviously--

00:42:52.270 --> 00:42:53.471 align:middle line:90%
it's a holiday weekend.

00:42:53.471 --> 00:42:58.777 align:middle line:84%
So there's a large traffic
jam or you mentioned

00:42:58.777 --> 00:43:01.479 align:middle line:90%
in airport lines or in--

00:43:01.479 --> 00:43:03.615 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Or riding in
wheelchairs I've had to do in--

00:43:03.615 --> 00:43:06.751 align:middle line:84%
with a lot of my travel
last one and a half months.

00:43:06.751 --> 00:43:12.691 align:middle line:84%
You know, I'm not perfected,
I could get irritated,

00:43:12.691 --> 00:43:15.560 align:middle line:84%
but as soon as I see
myself doing that to myself,

00:43:15.560 --> 00:43:18.797 align:middle line:84%
I'd basically start
breathing just the way we were

00:43:18.797 --> 00:43:20.165 align:middle line:90%
demonstrating it.

00:43:20.165 --> 00:43:22.867 align:middle line:84%
And I mean, it's a choice,
it's a choice is I--

00:43:22.867 --> 00:43:24.803 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to poison
myself because I'm

00:43:24.803 --> 00:43:27.172 align:middle line:84%
out of control because, you
know, maybe I'm not going

00:43:27.172 --> 00:43:28.440 align:middle line:90%
to make the appointment.

00:43:28.440 --> 00:43:30.342 align:middle line:84%
The people in that traffic
jam, they just may not get

00:43:30.342 --> 00:43:32.043 align:middle line:84%
to where they want to get
to, when they get there--

00:43:32.043 --> 00:43:33.378 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right, right.

00:43:33.378 --> 00:43:35.980 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And I can empathize
without frustrating that is--

00:43:35.980 --> 00:43:38.683 align:middle line:84%
and yet it's a wonderful
place to practice.

00:43:38.683 --> 00:43:41.586 align:middle line:84%
Practice breathing, practice
letting go of any story.

00:43:41.586 --> 00:43:43.955 align:middle line:84%
If you say for example, I have
to get to that appointment.

00:43:43.955 --> 00:43:45.256 align:middle line:90%
You're going to be miserable.

00:43:45.256 --> 00:43:49.027 align:middle line:84%
If you say, "OK, what is
actually have to do right now?"

00:43:49.027 --> 00:43:51.496 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm just sitting in
a car that's hardly moving.

00:43:51.496 --> 00:43:52.464 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right, right.

00:43:52.464 --> 00:43:54.165 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And your body
becomes spacious

00:43:54.165 --> 00:43:56.801 align:middle line:84%
and you become at
peace in yourself.

00:43:56.801 --> 00:43:58.837 align:middle line:84%
Well, at least even if you're
not getting to where you need

00:43:58.837 --> 00:44:01.206 align:middle line:84%
to get to, you're not
poisoning yourself.

00:44:01.206 --> 00:44:05.443 align:middle line:84%
And that actually-- that
quality of your own presence,

00:44:05.443 --> 00:44:08.179 align:middle line:84%
that purity of your own
presence is a gift to all

00:44:08.179 --> 00:44:10.582 align:middle line:84%
of existence, it
radiates from you.

00:44:10.582 --> 00:44:13.485 align:middle line:84%
When I say who-- or
begins now, who we--

00:44:13.485 --> 00:44:16.354 align:middle line:90%
we will ever be begins now.

00:44:16.354 --> 00:44:19.124 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Well I'm thinking
about that maybe, I mean,

00:44:19.124 --> 00:44:21.626 align:middle line:84%
there's an accident obviously
that stopped the traffic,

00:44:21.626 --> 00:44:24.696 align:middle line:84%
and the person that's in
that's accident, so let's talk

00:44:24.696 --> 00:44:27.265 align:middle line:84%
about that, when you're
in that place of crisis,

00:44:27.265 --> 00:44:30.535 align:middle line:90%
how do you use this to heal?

00:44:30.535 --> 00:44:36.040 align:middle line:84%
I mean to heal from the
inside out, to heal the body?

00:44:36.040 --> 00:44:38.643 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Well as I said, you know,
from being a reactive man four

00:44:38.643 --> 00:44:41.880 align:middle line:84%
and a half months ago, I
developed severe hip pain,

00:44:41.880 --> 00:44:44.983 align:middle line:84%
today I came in there
with crutches just barely

00:44:44.983 --> 00:44:48.653 align:middle line:84%
after being riding in the
airport and, you know,

00:44:48.653 --> 00:44:50.622 align:middle line:84%
through the airports
and wheelchairs.

00:44:50.622 --> 00:44:53.858 align:middle line:84%
Woman trying to push me up
some steep ramps and struggling

00:44:53.858 --> 00:44:57.762 align:middle line:84%
and just giving their
hearts and-- if you don't--

00:44:57.762 --> 00:45:00.131 align:middle line:84%
I don't tell myself a story
that life should be different

00:45:00.131 --> 00:45:04.068 align:middle line:84%
than it is, and therefor where I
am is exactly how it should be.

00:45:04.068 --> 00:45:09.207 align:middle line:84%
And as far as somebody
that's been injured I know

00:45:09.207 --> 00:45:14.579 align:middle line:84%
that once I was in a very bad
car accident I can just barely

00:45:14.579 --> 00:45:17.382 align:middle line:84%
crawl out, I got to the
side of the road and I knew

00:45:17.382 --> 00:45:20.351 align:middle line:84%
that if there was going to
be any injury in my body,

00:45:20.351 --> 00:45:23.154 align:middle line:84%
it was being imprinted at he
level of energy of the moment

00:45:23.154 --> 00:45:25.690 align:middle line:84%
of the collision, and that
was such a deeper energy

00:45:25.690 --> 00:45:29.093 align:middle line:84%
than my ordinary state
that I took myself back

00:45:29.093 --> 00:45:31.496 align:middle line:84%
through soft breathing,
bigger and bigger,

00:45:31.496 --> 00:45:33.531 align:middle line:84%
more and more expansive
till I felt I was

00:45:33.531 --> 00:45:38.036 align:middle line:84%
in the exact same state as
where did the impact took place

00:45:38.036 --> 00:45:39.771 align:middle line:90%
and I had my body just release,

00:45:39.771 --> 00:45:42.073 align:middle line:84%
anything that it
might have taken

00:45:42.073 --> 00:45:43.274 align:middle line:90%
on at the moment of impact.

00:45:43.274 --> 00:45:45.009 align:middle line:90%
The policemen say, "Are you OK?"

00:45:45.009 --> 00:45:47.512 align:middle line:84%
I suggest I just need
a few more minutes.

00:45:47.512 --> 00:45:49.080 align:middle line:84%
And then after that it
was just a little bit

00:45:49.080 --> 00:45:50.815 align:middle line:90%
of massage, and chiropractic.

00:45:50.815 --> 00:45:54.719 align:middle line:84%
Yet the car was totaled, I was
upside down in the back seat

00:45:54.719 --> 00:45:59.524 align:middle line:84%
where my front seat had been--
it didn't exist anymore.

00:45:59.524 --> 00:46:02.227 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, there was a
good deal of fortune in that,

00:46:02.227 --> 00:46:05.663 align:middle line:84%
but I also knew that--
that the-- the--

00:46:05.663 --> 00:46:08.333 align:middle line:84%
the trauma takes place
at a particular level

00:46:08.333 --> 00:46:11.970 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness and I know how
to put myself back to that level

00:46:11.970 --> 00:46:13.304 align:middle line:90%
and release the trauma.

00:46:13.304 --> 00:46:15.573 align:middle line:84%
That can be taught to people
and I do it all the time.

00:46:15.573 --> 00:46:16.808 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: My goodness, wow.

00:46:16.808 --> 00:46:18.176 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: All the time.

00:46:18.176 --> 00:46:19.911 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Wow, that's a-- that's
an amazing story to be able

00:46:19.911 --> 00:46:21.880 align:middle line:90%
to go even many, many years

00:46:21.880 --> 00:46:24.816 align:middle line:84%
after an accident would have
happened and that's incredible.

00:46:24.816 --> 00:46:27.285 align:middle line:84%
All right so you talked
a little bit earlier

00:46:27.285 --> 00:46:28.686 align:middle line:90%
about the art of listening.

00:46:28.686 --> 00:46:31.623 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take a look at
this video that talks about how

00:46:31.623 --> 00:46:34.392 align:middle line:84%
to really actively listen,
this is a beautiful piece.

00:46:34.392 --> 00:46:38.496 align:middle line:84%
I want-- I want you all
to take a look at this.

00:46:38.496 --> 00:46:39.964 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: I just want
to share a few--

00:46:39.964 --> 00:46:45.870 align:middle line:84%
just a few simple
things as a gift,

00:46:45.870 --> 00:46:49.774 align:middle line:84%
something that I keep
practicing and keep learning.

00:46:49.774 --> 00:46:53.778 align:middle line:84%
About listening, about how
we are present for each other

00:46:53.778 --> 00:46:56.915 align:middle line:90%
in conversation, how we listen.

00:46:56.915 --> 00:47:02.654 align:middle line:84%
So the first and it's
really obvious pay attention

00:47:02.654 --> 00:47:08.159 align:middle line:84%
to what's someone saying
and wait till they finish.

00:47:08.159 --> 00:47:12.463 align:middle line:84%
Wail till you have a sense
they've completed their thought,

00:47:12.463 --> 00:47:15.133 align:middle line:90%
even check, you know.

00:47:15.133 --> 00:47:17.936 align:middle line:90%
Did you finish?

00:47:17.936 --> 00:47:21.506 align:middle line:84%
It's so easy to talk
over another person.

00:47:21.506 --> 00:47:26.110 align:middle line:84%
It's so easy to try to complete
their sentences, it's-- it--

00:47:26.110 --> 00:47:28.846 align:middle line:84%
it's this tendency many of
us have to think we know

00:47:28.846 --> 00:47:31.816 align:middle line:90%
where someone else is going.

00:47:31.816 --> 00:47:34.485 align:middle line:84%
What changes when you listen
in this way is the field

00:47:34.485 --> 00:47:38.256 align:middle line:90%
of the relationship itself.

00:47:38.256 --> 00:47:41.960 align:middle line:84%
When you have really heard
someone and you wait for them

00:47:41.960 --> 00:47:45.697 align:middle line:84%
to finish, sometimes
what you would have said

00:47:45.697 --> 00:47:47.532 align:middle line:90%
if you would spoken right on top

00:47:47.532 --> 00:47:50.168 align:middle line:84%
of them isn't even
necessary anymore.

00:47:50.168 --> 00:47:53.304 align:middle line:84%
And you can bring something
that's completely fresh.

00:47:53.304 --> 00:47:55.006 align:middle line:84%
Or you bring something
that really adds

00:47:55.006 --> 00:47:58.376 align:middle line:90%
to what the other person said.

00:47:58.376 --> 00:48:02.413 align:middle line:84%
So try to just be very,
very conscious of the habit

00:48:02.413 --> 00:48:04.615 align:middle line:84%
of talking over people
or the habit

00:48:04.615 --> 00:48:06.651 align:middle line:90%
of completing their sentences.

00:48:06.651 --> 00:48:09.587 align:middle line:84%
I think it's kind of a
problem sometimes men have

00:48:09.587 --> 00:48:11.789 align:middle line:90%
with their women.

00:48:13.358 --> 00:48:20.665 align:middle line:84%
Second thing is when we are
listening from early childhood,

00:48:20.665 --> 00:48:22.500 align:middle line:90%
we have listened to see whether

00:48:22.500 --> 00:48:25.069 align:middle line:84%
or not what someone
is saying is going

00:48:25.069 --> 00:48:27.205 align:middle line:84%
to threaten us or
be good for us.

00:48:27.205 --> 00:48:32.844 align:middle line:84%
Are we going to be judged or put
in a negative sense or praised?

00:48:32.844 --> 00:48:37.782 align:middle line:84%
See if you can shift your
listening from agreement,

00:48:37.782 --> 00:48:40.451 align:middle line:84%
the mode of, "Do I
agree or do I not agree

00:48:40.451 --> 00:48:42.220 align:middle line:90%
with what this person has said."

00:48:42.220 --> 00:48:45.156 align:middle line:84%
And instead see if
you can listen just

00:48:45.156 --> 00:48:47.125 align:middle line:84%
to what the other
person is saying.

00:48:47.125 --> 00:48:51.963 align:middle line:84%
See if you can again
sense the difference

00:48:51.963 --> 00:48:56.167 align:middle line:84%
between unconsciously listening
for agreement or disagreement.

00:48:56.167 --> 00:48:59.337 align:middle line:84%
If they agree you're
safe and you add to it.

00:48:59.337 --> 00:49:02.807 align:middle line:84%
If you disagree then you have
to take a different position

00:49:02.807 --> 00:49:06.277 align:middle line:84%
and maybe defend yourself or
find the fault of the flaw

00:49:06.277 --> 00:49:08.212 align:middle line:84%
in what the other
person is saying.

00:49:08.212 --> 00:49:11.849 align:middle line:84%
And so what then is the
relationship consecrated

00:49:11.849 --> 00:49:13.351 align:middle line:90%
to unconsciously?

00:49:13.351 --> 00:49:15.420 align:middle line:90%
It's distrust.

00:49:15.420 --> 00:49:18.389 align:middle line:84%
Unconsciously when we
listen for agreement

00:49:18.389 --> 00:49:24.529 align:middle line:84%
and disagreement we're listening
for trust and distrust.

00:49:24.529 --> 00:49:28.566 align:middle line:84%
But it's trust and distrust
of another, of a situation,

00:49:28.566 --> 00:49:31.569 align:middle line:84%
it's not a deep sense of
connection to yourself

00:49:31.569 --> 00:49:35.239 align:middle line:84%
where you have trust
intrinsically and independent

00:49:35.239 --> 00:49:36.507 align:middle line:90%
of what someone else says.

00:49:36.507 --> 00:49:40.778 align:middle line:84%
So this practice, see
if you can be aware

00:49:40.778 --> 00:49:44.682 align:middle line:84%
of whether you are listening
in the mode of agreement

00:49:44.682 --> 00:49:47.952 align:middle line:84%
or disagreement and see if
you can just put it aside.

00:49:47.952 --> 00:49:50.455 align:middle line:84%
It really doesn't
matter if you agree.

00:49:50.455 --> 00:49:52.023 align:middle line:84%
What is that other
person saying?

00:49:52.023 --> 00:49:52.723 align:middle line:90%
It's their truth.

00:49:52.723 --> 00:49:53.758 align:middle line:90%
It's their perspective.

00:49:53.758 --> 00:49:56.160 align:middle line:90%
It's their opinion.

00:49:56.160 --> 00:49:57.495 align:middle line:84%
Whether you agree
doesn't matter,

00:49:57.495 --> 00:49:59.730 align:middle line:84%
whether you disagree
doesn't matter

00:49:59.730 --> 00:50:04.469 align:middle line:84%
if what you want is a
relational field that starts

00:50:04.469 --> 00:50:13.044 align:middle line:84%
to support a higher energy,
a deep presence of trust,

00:50:13.044 --> 00:50:17.448 align:middle line:84%
settles process that
arises really within us.

00:50:17.448 --> 00:50:19.417 align:middle line:90%
So these two things, just

00:50:19.417 --> 00:50:23.454 align:middle line:84%
to be conscious let people
finish their sentence really,

00:50:23.454 --> 00:50:30.828 align:middle line:84%
really listen and don't
listen through the filter

00:50:30.828 --> 00:50:33.598 align:middle line:90%
of agreement-disagreement.

00:50:33.598 --> 00:50:35.266 align:middle line:90%
It's an experiment.

00:50:35.266 --> 00:50:38.035 align:middle line:90%
What very few of us realizes,

00:50:38.035 --> 00:50:41.439 align:middle line:84%
we are inventing the
possibility of intimacy.

00:50:41.439 --> 00:50:45.076 align:middle line:84%
We are inventing a
possibility of relationship.

00:50:45.076 --> 00:50:46.043 align:middle line:90%
There are no fixed rules.

00:50:46.043 --> 00:50:48.246 align:middle line:84%
There never have
been fixed rules.

00:50:48.246 --> 00:50:49.881 align:middle line:84%
There are things that
work better than others.

00:50:49.881 --> 00:50:54.185 align:middle line:84%
And as Einstein said, "If you
keep doing the same things over

00:50:54.185 --> 00:50:56.888 align:middle line:84%
and over again and
expect different results,

00:50:56.888 --> 00:50:58.322 align:middle line:90%
that's crazy."

00:50:58.322 --> 00:51:03.227 align:middle line:84%
If we keep listening to others
through the lens agreement

00:51:03.227 --> 00:51:07.465 align:middle line:84%
and disagreement and expect
to have a real sense of trust

00:51:07.465 --> 00:51:11.435 align:middle line:84%
and [inaudible] an inexplicable
sense of connection to grow

00:51:11.435 --> 00:51:14.705 align:middle line:84%
in that relationship,
it will never happen.

00:51:14.705 --> 00:51:17.875 align:middle line:84%
You'll agree with people, those
would be the ones you side with.

00:51:17.875 --> 00:51:19.143 align:middle line:90%
You'll disagree with people.

00:51:19.143 --> 00:51:21.345 align:middle line:84%
Those are the ones
you'll polarize with.

00:51:21.345 --> 00:51:25.116 align:middle line:84%
And a deeper field that is there
for all of you conversations

00:51:25.116 --> 00:51:29.754 align:middle line:84%
and all of your relationships,
it won't take shape.

00:51:29.754 --> 00:51:32.857 align:middle line:84%
So that's just my little
offering for right now.

00:51:32.857 --> 00:51:36.060 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So how would one use
a sense of expansiveness

00:51:36.060 --> 00:51:38.629 align:middle line:84%
when they can't pay their
mortgage or can't pay their rent

00:51:38.629 --> 00:51:41.833 align:middle line:84%
and looking and the check
is not going to clear?

00:51:41.833 --> 00:51:43.467 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Expansiveness
is only one-half

00:51:43.467 --> 00:51:45.636 align:middle line:84%
of what it means to
be really present.

00:51:45.636 --> 00:51:48.940 align:middle line:84%
You have to be focused
and expansive.

00:51:48.940 --> 00:51:51.876 align:middle line:84%
You can't-- There's no--
There's no magic bullet

00:51:51.876 --> 00:51:53.344 align:middle line:90%
to paying your bills.

00:51:53.344 --> 00:51:56.514 align:middle line:84%
If yo can't pay your bills, what
lifestyle are you attached to?

00:51:56.514 --> 00:51:59.283 align:middle line:84%
You know, simplify,
simplify, simplify.

00:51:59.283 --> 00:52:02.053 align:middle line:84%
A person who lives
in the present more

00:52:02.053 --> 00:52:04.188 align:middle line:90%
and more is filled from within.

00:52:04.188 --> 00:52:06.390 align:middle line:84%
So you need less and
less room without.

00:52:06.390 --> 00:52:09.227 align:middle line:84%
I know this personally for
myself 'cause I've chosen

00:52:09.227 --> 00:52:12.296 align:middle line:84%
to not live in a multimillion
dollar house anymore.

00:52:12.296 --> 00:52:14.398 align:middle line:84%
To give that away years
ago in a marriage to live

00:52:14.398 --> 00:52:19.203 align:middle line:84%
in something exceptionally
simple, because it's--

00:52:19.203 --> 00:52:22.039 align:middle line:84%
it's just the flowers, that's
the light, it's the tone

00:52:22.039 --> 00:52:24.775 align:middle line:84%
of voice in people
that can fill anyone.

00:52:24.775 --> 00:52:29.513 align:middle line:84%
So we live in a society that
has created soul-deadening debt,

00:52:29.513 --> 00:52:33.050 align:middle line:84%
and millions even billions
of people worldwide,

00:52:33.050 --> 00:52:36.988 align:middle line:84%
you have to make a choice
to walk away from that.

00:52:36.988 --> 00:52:38.155 align:middle line:90%
And when you do, you have--

00:52:38.155 --> 00:52:40.925 align:middle line:84%
you can't confuse money
with your identity.

00:52:40.925 --> 00:52:44.228 align:middle line:84%
The people that are paid a lot
of money, millions of dollars

00:52:44.228 --> 00:52:46.297 align:middle line:84%
from an incorporations
look in a mirror

00:52:46.297 --> 00:52:48.766 align:middle line:84%
and they believe they
deserve that amount of money,

00:52:48.766 --> 00:52:51.969 align:middle line:84%
and if they lose it that's
someone's taking their self away

00:52:51.969 --> 00:52:54.071 align:middle line:90%
from them, that's impossible.

00:52:54.071 --> 00:52:57.341 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Soul-deadening debt,
that is very powerful word, yes.

00:52:57.341 --> 00:52:58.476 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yeah.

00:52:58.476 --> 00:53:00.845 align:middle line:84%
And don't let yourself
be so deadened by debt.

00:53:00.845 --> 00:53:04.482 align:middle line:84%
Get rid of it, simplify, shrink,
if you can't afford to live

00:53:04.482 --> 00:53:07.351 align:middle line:84%
in a community this expensive
on the income you're making

00:53:07.351 --> 00:53:09.553 align:middle line:84%
and you can't get much out
of your house right now,

00:53:09.553 --> 00:53:12.290 align:middle line:84%
then move to a community where
you can afford to buy something

00:53:12.290 --> 00:53:13.958 align:middle line:90%
and very modest and simple.

00:53:13.958 --> 00:53:16.394 align:middle line:84%
My life in Ohio, I
couldn't, at this point,

00:53:16.394 --> 00:53:21.098 align:middle line:84%
go back in buy house there, but
I live wonderfully in Colorado.

00:53:21.098 --> 00:53:24.201 align:middle line:84%
And the environment is just
as delicious for me, different

00:53:24.201 --> 00:53:26.404 align:middle line:90%
but just as the delicious.

00:53:26.404 --> 00:53:28.806 align:middle line:90%
It's a choice you make.

00:53:28.806 --> 00:53:30.274 align:middle line:84%
What we have to understand
is we're here

00:53:30.274 --> 00:53:32.410 align:middle line:84%
on this planet to
invent ourselves.

00:53:32.410 --> 00:53:35.146 align:middle line:84%
That's what spirituality
really is.

00:53:35.146 --> 00:53:38.616 align:middle line:84%
You start out, you're
programmed, you're conditioned,

00:53:38.616 --> 00:53:42.153 align:middle line:84%
you're enculturated, you decide
through your consecration,

00:53:42.153 --> 00:53:44.889 align:middle line:84%
through your practice,
moment by moment the kind

00:53:44.889 --> 00:53:46.891 align:middle line:90%
of human being you want to be.

00:53:46.891 --> 00:53:50.461 align:middle line:84%
And if you want to spend your
life constantly facing this

00:53:50.461 --> 00:53:53.464 align:middle line:90%
threat of debt and being in a--

00:53:53.464 --> 00:53:56.100 align:middle line:84%
almost perpetual
soul-deadening contraction,

00:53:56.100 --> 00:53:58.936 align:middle line:90%
what a sorry thing to choose.

00:53:58.936 --> 00:54:00.905 align:middle line:84%
And that a society
would build itself

00:54:00.905 --> 00:54:04.075 align:middle line:90%
that way is strange to me.

00:54:04.075 --> 00:54:07.111 align:middle line:84%
But I have chosen
and a lot of people

00:54:07.111 --> 00:54:10.081 align:middle line:84%
that I have helped guide
have chosen to live much,

00:54:10.081 --> 00:54:13.484 align:middle line:84%
much simpler lives where
the fulfillment comes

00:54:13.484 --> 00:54:17.822 align:middle line:84%
with this breath with how
I am present to what is

00:54:17.822 --> 00:54:20.324 align:middle line:84%
and that's a much
healthier life.

00:54:20.324 --> 00:54:22.293 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: You don't say that
from a place of lack.

00:54:22.293 --> 00:54:24.462 align:middle line:84%
You don't say that from
place of victimhood.

00:54:24.462 --> 00:54:27.098 align:middle line:84%
You don't say, "Well, I'm not
making enough money so I have

00:54:27.098 --> 00:54:28.699 align:middle line:90%
to live in this other place."

00:54:28.699 --> 00:54:30.901 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: I would never say
that to me, because if I said

00:54:30.901 --> 00:54:33.771 align:middle line:84%
that I would make myself
unhappy in the now,

00:54:33.771 --> 00:54:35.473 align:middle line:84%
which is the only
thing that lives.

00:54:35.473 --> 00:54:37.074 align:middle line:90%
The only time we are is now.

00:54:37.074 --> 00:54:41.746 align:middle line:84%
If I said this-- this house
isn't as nice as the other one,

00:54:41.746 --> 00:54:43.948 align:middle line:90%
OK, that's-- if I'm saying, "OK,

00:54:43.948 --> 00:54:46.250 align:middle line:84%
there isn't the granite
counter top and below."

00:54:46.250 --> 00:54:47.418 align:middle line:90%
Yes that's factual.

00:54:47.418 --> 00:54:49.487 align:middle line:84%
But what I'm really
saying is, "Well,

00:54:49.487 --> 00:54:52.156 align:middle line:84%
this house doesn't
mirror my importance

00:54:52.156 --> 00:54:53.357 align:middle line:90%
that way the other one did."

00:54:53.357 --> 00:54:56.627 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't waste one
split second on a thought

00:54:56.627 --> 00:54:58.429 align:middle line:90%
that makes my body contract.

00:54:58.429 --> 00:55:02.099 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Gosh, if there is
anything that people get

00:55:02.099 --> 00:55:04.935 align:middle line:84%
from this show that
is so important.

00:55:04.935 --> 00:55:07.772 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: That is the practice,
transforming your life

00:55:07.772 --> 00:55:10.474 align:middle line:84%
through the power of
presence means I am not going

00:55:10.474 --> 00:55:13.511 align:middle line:84%
to let a future thought or
a past thought or judgment

00:55:13.511 --> 00:55:16.147 align:middle line:84%
of another or a situation
or of a house--

00:55:16.147 --> 00:55:17.548 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Or a conversation.

00:55:17.548 --> 00:55:20.684 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: -- or a conversation or
myself put me into contraction.

00:55:20.684 --> 00:55:22.119 align:middle line:84%
And if the people who
are listening said

00:55:22.119 --> 00:55:25.456 align:middle line:84%
that that's not possible,
the answer is you hear--

00:55:25.456 --> 00:55:27.992 align:middle line:84%
you heard a man even play a
violin and you by a violin

00:55:27.992 --> 00:55:29.794 align:middle line:90%
and you can't play it at all,

00:55:29.794 --> 00:55:31.929 align:middle line:84%
but 10,000 hours later
you're pretty good

00:55:31.929 --> 00:55:35.099 align:middle line:84%
and 20,000 hours later
you're Yehudi Menuhin.

00:55:35.099 --> 00:55:36.066 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: So it's practice?

00:55:36.066 --> 00:55:37.568 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And practice,
and practice,

00:55:37.568 --> 00:55:40.037 align:middle line:84%
this is my path,
I've practiced it.

00:55:40.037 --> 00:55:42.506 align:middle line:84%
